column1:
Discover marketing considerations for non-profits . A non-profit organization ( also known as an NPO ) is an organization that does not pay for its own overhead and that relies on the generosity of individuals, private foundations, corporate and governmental agencies, and others to make its mission and operations possible. These organizations typically have one or several of the following characteristics: They are small or very small;

They are operating in an environment that is challenging and that requires high levels of organization and focus; and

They often rely on the generosity of others to help them operate and make a difference.
